PN,39203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1776334011
OL,3,CLast minute deal reached to save 180-
OL,4,Cyear-old ferry crossing's short-term
OL,5,Cfuture
OL,7,FCouncillor Michael Vincent, Leader of
OL,8,FWyre Borough Council, said: "Wyre
OL,9,FCouncil's officers and Cabinet have
OL,10,Fbeen working tirelessly to secure the
OL,11,Ffuture of the ferry, and I am
OL,12,Fdelighted that we have been able to
OL,13,Fagree a way forward that will see the
OL,14,Fservice continue."
OL,16,F"Our focus now turns to securing the
OL,17,Fferry's longterm future, so residents
OL,18,Fand visitors can have confidence in
OL,19,Fthe service for years to come."
OL,26,@pD@]OUxD@AOU{D@_O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
